The Vice President, Mike Pence, chaired the inaugural meeting of the reconstituted National Space Council at the Steven F. Udvar-Hazy Center in Virginia. In his speech, Pence emphasized President Donald Trump's commitment to American leadership in space and the need for a coherent vision and policy for outer space. He expressed concern over the United States' loss of leadership in space and outlined the objectives of the National Space Council, which include maintaining a commercial and human presence in low-Earth orbit, returning American astronauts to the moon, and advancing space technology to protect national security. Pence also highlighted the importance of partnerships with industry and the need to inspire future generations to pursue education in science, technology, engineering, and math. The meeting concluded with plans to form a National Space Council Advisory Group to provide recommendations for the council's policies.